<div id="bookReviews">
  




  <div class="friendReviews elementListBrown" >
    <div class="section firstReview">
      

<div id="review_1779072852" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1779072852" />
    <a title="J. Schlenker" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/2196210-j-schlenker"><img alt="J. Schlenker" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1603117586p2/2196210.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1779072852?book_show_action=true">Oct 08, 2016</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="J. Schlenker" class="user" itemprop="url" name="J. Schlenker" href="/user/show/2196210-j-schlenker">J. Schlenker</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1779072852" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17037482250652078004">I’m certainly glad Mr. Brodt decided to tell his story. I’ve watched my share of documentaries on the Holocaust, and think Hank Brodt’s story would make an excellent one. With each sharing of someone’s experience of the Holocaust, I learn something new. I didn’t realize that prisoners were shuffled around to different camps. It amazes me how much torture some can endure. I still imagined the suffering to be much greater than even what I was reading, although what I read was bad enough. I believe</span>
  <span id="freeText17037482250652078004" style="display:none">I’m certainly glad Mr. Brodt decided to tell his story. I’ve watched my share of documentaries on the Holocaust, and think Hank Brodt’s story would make an excellent one. With each sharing of someone’s experience of the Holocaust, I learn something new. I didn’t realize that prisoners were shuffled around to different camps. It amazes me how much torture some can endure. I still imagined the suffering to be much greater than even what I was reading, although what I read was bad enough. I believe it was said that this was started by one man. I tend to disagree with that. I think it takes a lot of people to start or cause something like this, from all those with such evil in their hearts that they would readily go along with one man and treat other human beings like this to the ones who turned a blind eye to what was happening. Some of us are guilty, but all of us are responsible. Still you wonder why this happens, and what lessons are to learned. Mr. Brodt turned his experience around in helping others to understand and by becoming an excellent husband, father and citizen.<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="17037482250652078004" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


