        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1771094301" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17013429090007089382">This book is nothing short of an emotional journey that left me feeling bereft yet so full of hope. This is the story of Hank, a Holocaust survivor told through the writing of his daughter Deb. Hank was 90 when he finally decided to tell his story and his daughter is trained trauma specialist so this story was done with great care. This book had me starting and stopping frequently, but it was more so that I could take a moment to gather my own thoughts and feelings about what Hank endured. From </span>
  <span id="freeText17013429090007089382" style="display:none">This book is nothing short of an emotional journey that left me feeling bereft yet so full of hope. This is the story of Hank, a Holocaust survivor told through the writing of his daughter Deb. Hank was 90 when he finally decided to tell his story and his daughter is trained trauma specialist so this story was done with great care. This book had me starting and stopping frequently, but it was more so that I could take a moment to gather my own thoughts and feelings about what Hank endured. From his life with his family and the orphanage he was forced to move into, to the various concentration camps where he was nearly worked to death, I felt like I was right there with him. It is made clear that this is not just a story of a survivor, but of a man who truly lived his life and that is the quite possibly the greatest payback to those who sought to destroy him for the simple fact of being Jewish.<br />I highly recommend this book to anyone with a desire to learn about the atrocities of the Holocaust. This was very well done!<br /><br />I received a copy of this in exchange for an honest review</span>
  <a data-text-id="17013429090007089382" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

