<div id="review_2676065632" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2676065632" />
    <a title="Ganessa Press" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/82267110-ganessa-press"><img alt="Ganessa Press" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_50x66-632230dc9882b4352d753eedf9396530.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2676065632?book_show_action=true">Jan 17, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Ganessa Press" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Ganessa Press" href="/user/show/82267110-ganessa-press">Ganessa Press</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/32467262-hank-brodt-holocaust-memoirs">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2676065632" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16679049746575560460"><strong>This man is the epitome of a ‘survivor’...</strong><br/><br/>Wow. Simply unreal, yet unfortunately, it is very real. Thank God there are wonderfully brave survivors like Me Brondt, who along with help from his supportive family, had the courage to relive the horrors of WWII, and primarily the concentration camps, in order to write this book. With most of these survivors sadly being gone now, we will only have the written testimonies left to read about, and in which to teach future generations. It is so important t</span>
  <span id="freeText16679049746575560460" style="display:none"><strong>This man is the epitome of a ‘survivor’...</strong><br /><br />Wow. Simply unreal, yet unfortunately, it is very real. Thank God there are wonderfully brave survivors like Me Brondt, who along with help from his supportive family, had the courage to relive the horrors of WWII, and primarily the concentration camps, in order to write this book. With most of these survivors sadly being gone now, we will only have the written testimonies left to read about, and in which to teach future generations. It is so important that we have these accounts of the real atrocities so that history won’t ever repeat itself. Mr Brodt went through hell for 6 years of his life at the hands of the Nazis in every way possible, yet somehow he got through it, while still holding on to his own humanity, dignity, and sense of right and wrong. Despite the horrendous treatment and killings he saw all that time, he didn’t let it change him inside, and he carried his pride in being Jewish in whatever ways he could, if only inside his mind. He never let it go. He is a hero in my eyes. Thank you for this book and the very realistic way it goes through the years with such extraordinary clarity. It is so unbelievably detailed that I genuinely felt like I was with Mr Brodt going through those awful and life changing events with him. God Bless him and his family. </span>
  <a data-text-id="16679049746575560460" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


