              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6802182793392551894">I am lucky because Hank Brodt is a dear friend of mine. I met him through an effort to bring Holocaust awareness to my college campus in North Carolina a few years ago and he has been an integral part of my life ever since. He is a friend, inspiration, confidant, teacher, and adopted-grandfather. I cannot stress enough how important it has been in my life and will forever be my mission to share his story and to honor all those who we have tragically lost during these events in our history. Pleas</span>
  <span id="freeText6802182793392551894" style="display:none">I am lucky because Hank Brodt is a dear friend of mine. I met him through an effort to bring Holocaust awareness to my college campus in North Carolina a few years ago and he has been an integral part of my life ever since. He is a friend, inspiration, confidant, teacher, and adopted-grandfather. I cannot stress enough how important it has been in my life and will forever be my mission to share his story and to honor all those who we have tragically lost during these events in our history. Please read this story and pass it along to others. Start a conversation. Do not let these stories become just stories... they are real, raw and important to our history. Hank will always have a place in my heart and I will always do whatever I can to honor his life story, both the tragedies and the high points. Thank you, Hank.</span>
