<span id="freeTextContainer1440200683903510672">The time before, during and after the Holocaust are described in this survivor’s memoir.<br/><br/>I found this book very moving. The first hand account of the hardship / evil / betrayals that all individuals decimated by the Holocaust suffered was compelling and the straight forward language / short chapters made it ‘easy’ to process the horrors being described.<br/><br/>The two things that I took away from this book were, firstly the great courage / determination shown by many survivor’s (of man’s inhumanity) to t</span>
  <span id="freeText1440200683903510672" style="display:none">The time before, during and after the Holocaust are described in this survivor’s memoir.<br /><br />I found this book very moving. The first hand account of the hardship / evil / betrayals that all individuals decimated by the Holocaust suffered was compelling and the straight forward language / short chapters made it ‘easy’ to process the horrors being described.<br /><br />The two things that I took away from this book were, firstly the great courage / determination shown by many survivor’s (of man’s inhumanity) to triumph by living a good / productive life is a cause for hope and secondly people can easily be lead into acts of barbarity.<br /><br />I would recommend this book to anyone who doubts that humans have great power for evil and also great strength to conquer adversity.</span>
