<div id="review_4425626122" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4425626122" />
    <a title="linda murray" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/129002810-linda-murray"><img alt="linda murray" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_50x66-632230dc9882b4352d753eedf9396530.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4425626122?book_show_action=true">Dec 30, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="linda murray" class="user" itemprop="url" name="linda murray" href="/user/show/129002810-linda-murray">linda murray</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/32467262-hank-brodt-holocaust-memoirs">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4425626122" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9463101180337784832"><strong>From a Boy to a Man in 4 Horrible Years</strong><br/><br/>I was born after WW2, but it was very much a part of my parents lives. Although they were American Christians, the horror that came out about what Hitler was doing to the Jews, left a sense of loathing, as many did, when the war ended and the stories of atrocities were revealed. Since I was a child I have read the stories that survivors have written, and Hank Brodts story is true. Those who deny it happened may someday find themselves in the same situation,</span>
  <span id="freeText9463101180337784832" style="display:none"><strong>From a Boy to a Man in 4 Horrible Years</strong><br /><br />I was born after WW2, but it was very much a part of my parents lives. Although they were American Christians, the horror that came out about what Hitler was doing to the Jews, left a sense of loathing, as many did, when the war ended and the stories of atrocities were revealed. Since I was a child I have read the stories that survivors have written, and Hank Brodts story is true. Those who deny it happened may someday find themselves in the same situation, but I would hope that we, as humans, will never forget and will step up again to liberate those being crushed. If you like to educate yourself, or your children, read this book. The story is true!<br /> <br />when the war ended and the stories of atrocities came</span>
