  <span id="freeText4447889911684766731" style="display:none"><strong>An honest account of surviving the Holocaust</strong><br /><br />I have read many heartbreaking stories of Holocaust survivors and time and time again I am amazed at their resilience and determination to live their lives after liberation to the fullest. This book tells the story of Hank Brodt, it is honest and Frank and is filled with tears and cheers. Thank you Hank for sharing your story, it should be included in the reading list of all junior schools, so that children from a young age can learn of the horrors brought on by racism, bigotry and sectarianism, children should learn that peace can only be preserved through tolerance acceptance and diversity across all walks of life</span>
